{{Quote|Look for us in the still depths of your mind.|The Leviathan Kithnarrock, telepathically communicating with a group of Jedi and their companions|<ref name="Valkyrie" />}}
The '''Leviathans''' were a [[Limb/Legends|tentacled]] [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]] residing on the [[Waterworld/Legends|waterworld]] [[Arrakan]]. The [[Millennium/Legends|thousand-year]]-old [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] Leviathan [[Kithnarrock]] was worshipped as a [[Deity/Legends|god]] by the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] [[Battrach/Legends|Battrach]] species, and during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], he helped a group of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and their companions [[Mission to Arrakan|reach]] a secret [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] sanctuary offworld.

==Biology and appearance==
The Leviathans were a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]]<ref name="Valkyrie" /> [[Species/Legends|species]],<ref name="Valkyrie" /><ref name="Drawing">{{SW|url=news/drawing-from-the-imagination-mythological-creatures-in-star-wars-part-1|text=Drawing from the Imagination: Mythological Creatures in ''Star Wars'', Part 1|int=Back from the Drawing Board|nolive=1}}</ref> members of which had multiple [[Limb/Legends|tentacles]] and at least one huge, ominous [[Eye/Legends|eye]].<ref name="Valkyrie" />

==History==
{{Quote|Who are you? What do you seek?|Kithnarrock, telepathically communicating with a group of Jedi and their companions|<ref name="Valkyrie" />}}
The Leviathans resided on the [[Waterworld/Legends|waterworld]] [[Arrakan]]. [[Kithnarrock]] was a vast Leviathan who was too large to be easily seen in his entirety and appeared as a mass of shadow and thrashing tentacles. He inhabited the depths of the [[Ocean/Legends|ocean]] on Arrakan and, by the time of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], had reached an age of one [[Millennium/Legends|thousand years]]. Kithnarrock was [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] and regularly communed with by the [[Duor]], the dominant sentient species on Arrakan, while the [[Battrach/Legends|Battrach]], another local species of sentients which had been [[Bioengineering/Legends|genetically engineered]] by the Duor, worshipped the Leviathan as a [[Deity/Legends|god]] and the creator of their [[Planet/Legends|world]].<ref name="Valkyrie" />

{{RPG|"[[Flight of the Jedi]]"}}
During the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Great Jedi Purge]] and the Galactic Civil War, a group of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and their companions [[Mission to Arrakan|traveled]] to Arrakan in order to learn the location of a secret offworld [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] sanctuary from a contact named "Narrock"&mdash;who, unbeknown to the group, was in reality Kithnarrock. The Duor eventually led the group to meet the Leviathan, who, after a [[Telepathy/Legends|telepathic]] conversation with them, planted the coordinates of the sanctuary in the subconscious of one of the Jedi's companions.<ref name="Valkyrie" />
{{Endgame}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Leviathans appeared in the second part of [[Phil Sidebotham]]'s [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] adventure "[[Flight of the Jedi]]," which was published in the Spring [[2000]] [[Valkyrie 20|twentieth issue]] of the ''[[Valkyrie]]'' magazine for use with [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''. Since that article was released outside of the [[Lucas Licensing]] process,<ref name="Valkyrie" /> it was considered non-[[canon]]ical with respect to the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity.<ref name="UnlicensedStatus">{{UnlicensedStatus}}</ref> However, the Leviathans specifically were indirectly mentioned in the [[October 17]], [[2013]] [[StarWars.com]] article "[https://web.archive.org/web/20140714085853/https://www.starwars.com/news/drawing-from-the-imagination-mythological-creatures-in-star-wars-part-1 Drawing from the Imagination: Mythological Creatures in ''Star Wars'', Part 1]."<ref name="Drawing" />

